{"id":38240,"title":"Perioperative considerations in the patient with Angelman syndrome.","abstract":"Angelman syndrome arises by one of 4 genetic mechanisms. Patients often have craniofacial abnormalities, vagal hypertonia, skeletal muscle atrophy or underdevelopment, a history of seizure disorders, and pharmacodynamic unpredictability. Its pathogenesis, clinical manifestations, diagnosis and treatment options, and perioperative anesthetic considerations are presented. ","date":"2014-03-07","categories":"Congenital Hereditary and Neonatal Diseases and Abnormalities","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24440034","annotations":[{"name":"Genetics","weight":0.804197,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Genetics"},{"name":"Skeletal striated muscle","weight":0.77158,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skeletal_striated_muscle"},{"name":"Muscle","weight":0.756683,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muscle"},{"name":"Atrophy","weight":0.736679,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Atrophy"},{"name":"Anesthetic","weight":0.698659,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anesthetic"},{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.697406,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Pathogenesis","weight":0.68384,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pathogenesis"},{"name":"Muscle atrophy","weight":0.678324,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Muscle_atrophy"},{"name":"Epileptic seizure","weight":0.678276,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epileptic_seizure"},{"name":"Syndrome","weight":0.673041,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Syndrome"},{"name":"Epilepsy","weight":0.660386,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epilepsy"},{"name":"Hypertonia","weight":0.635324,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hypertonia"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.603856,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"}